WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk was an outstanding individual, a devoted family man, and a
pillar of the American conservative movement; his passing leaves a void in our country that will
not be easily filled; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we designate September 10, 2026, as "Charlie Kirk Day" in the State of
Tennessee in remembrance of the life and legacy of that singular conservative icon, whose life
was cut short far too soon.
